Package: wrappify
Type: Package
Title: An R Wrapper for the Spotify API
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Aditya Saluja, Eric Baxter, Luka Vukovic
Maintainer: Eric Baxter <ebaxter271@gmail.com>
Description: This package provides users with a simple means for accessing the spotify API using their client credentials. Users can gather information on specific songs, artists, or podcasts using either a name or SPotify ID. Functionality is included to recieve information on related artists, top songs, recent podcast episodes, and song recomendations given parameters. 
Depends:
	R (>= 4.0)
Imports:
	glue, httr,	stringr (>= 1.4.0), ggplot2 (>= 3.3), dplyr (>= 1.0.2), tidyverse (>= 1.3.0), magrittr (>= 1.5), covr, knitr (>= 1.30), qpdf
VignetteBuilder: knitr
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    rmarkdown
